    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Alphabet of Semitic origin, borrowed from the Phoenecians in first millennium BCE, and modified by the Greeks to include characters representing both vowel and consonant sounds.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
